Project devoted to Bitcoin blockchain analysis using Bitcoin Core RPC and external market data.


1. rpc_to_parquet.py
Code used for the extraction of desired variables from the Bitcoin core using the RPC. The data is stored in parquets and a simple way of checkpoint saves is implemented.
This code uses the getblock() function with verbosity set to 2 to obtain even the desired variables regarding the individual transactions.
The results are in folders 'blocks/' and 'transactions/'.
The stored variables are: 
height, time, nTx, size, weight, fees, vsize and several other


2. btc_prices.parquet
Code used for the extraction of the Bitcoin prices for individual blocks. A Binance API is used to extract the prices at the time of the block origin. The values are again saved in parquets.
The results are stored in 'btc_prices.parquet'


3. analysis.py
Main code used for:
- visualization of quantities
- a study of Poisson distribution of time between blocks
- statistical and correlation analysis

The plots and histograms are stored in the folder 'plots/'.
